name: Nova Desk
summary: AI productivity cockpit for distributed teams
description: Nova Desk unifies task orchestration, knowledge surfacing, and collaborative AI copilots so hybrid teams can coordinate projects, meetings, and decision logs in a single workspace. The suite syncs tasks across PM tools, captures meeting insights automatically, and provides adaptive automations that remove busywork for fast-scaling companies.
features: AI copilots|Meeting transcripts|Unified inbox|Workflow templates|Offline mode

name: Blueprint Studio
description: Blueprint Studio accelerates interface design with AI-assisted wireframes, component-level collaboration, and continuous handoff to engineering. Designers co-create with generative layouts, version ideas quickly, and share accessible prototypes that sync bidirectionally with production codebases.
features: AI wireframes|Realtime feedback|Design QA|Component sync|Accessibility reports

name: Sentinel Core
description: Sentinel Core protects workstations with adaptive threat detection, decentralized policy orchestration, and encrypted telemetry exports. Security teams monitor fleets in real time, isolate compromised hosts instantly, and automate remediation workflows without sacrificing user productivity.
features: Behavioral AI|Playbooks|Offline isolation|SIEM export|Device posture

name: Lumen Note
description: Lumen Note helps students and researchers collect multimedia snippets, generate citations automatically, and collaborate on annotated outlines. Semantic search and timeline views make it easy to revisit sources and synthesize long-form findings across semesters.
features: Semantic search|Citation engine|Offline cache|Canvas mode|Multi-device sync

name: Nebula Engine
description: Nebula Engine ships a modular WebGPU runtime with cinematic rendering pipelines, XR tooling, and on-device asset optimizers. Indie studios deploy to browsers and desktops with a single codebase while retaining AAA lighting, physics, and audio fidelity.
features: WebGPU renderer|XR toolkit|Physics engine|Shader graph|Asset optimizer

name: Aurora Desk
description: Aurora Desk centralizes conversations, knowledge bases, and AI automations for SaaS support teams targeting sub-minute resolution times. Agents co-work with adaptive copilots, surface best responses instantly, and escalate with full context to engineering.
features: AI macros|Knowledge embeddings|Realtime analytics|Integrations|Role-based access

name: Flux Render
description: Flux Render delivers unbiased GPU render queues with collaborative shot review, USD pipelines, and color-managed deliveries. Creative agencies render campaign visuals faster while clients approve iterations inside an immersive viewer.
features: USD pipeline|ACES color|Shot review|Queue manager|GPU scaling

name: Pixel Forge
description: Pixel Forge pairs diffusion models with non-destructive editing, procedural brushes, and brand-safe outputs. Illustrators craft production-ready assets while retaining control over prompts, color palettes, and export formats.
features: Diffusion engine|Procedural brushes|Prompt history|Texture baking|Color controls

name: Gridwave Analytics
description: Gridwave Analytics enables data teams to query streaming and historical sources with SQL-first notebooks, auto-scaling compute, and governance guardrails. Analysts explore datasets collaboratively while operations teams monitor costs in real time.
features: Streaming SQL|Notebook branching|Lineage|Autoscaling|Access controls

name: Vector Hub
description: Vector Hub powers production AI workloads with IVF/PQ indexing, hybrid search, and evaluation dashboards. ML engineers deploy retrieval pipelines faster and observe quality drifts with configurable benchmarks.
features: Hybrid search|Embeddings toolkit|Model eval|Streaming ingestion|Usage analytics

name: Google Chrome
summary: Fast, secure, and widely adopted web browser
description: Google Chrome delivers a streamlined browsing experience with powerful developer tooling, automatic updates, synchronized profiles, and advanced phishing protection. Its V8 engine renders modern web applications efficiently while extensions and policies keep enterprise environments governed across devices.
features: Sandbox security|Sync across devices|Extension ecosystem|Built-in PDF viewer|Developer tools

name: Mozilla Firefox
description: Mozilla Firefox balances cutting-edge performance with strong privacy defaults, enhanced tracking protection, and extensive customization. It empowers users to audit permissions, isolate sites into containers, and leverage developer tools to debug complex web experiences in real time.
features: Enhanced tracking protection|Container tabs|Pocket integration|Developer tools|Sync

name: Microsoft Edge
description: Microsoft Edge combines Chromium speed with enterprise-grade security, shopping assistants, and deep integrations with Microsoft 365. Collections, vertical tabs, and responsive reading experiences help users research, compare, and share content across devices effortlessly.
features: Vertical tabs|Collections|Smart shopping|Password monitor|Immersive reader

name: Brave Browser
summary: Privacy-first Chromium browser with native blocking
description: Brave Browser blocks trackers and intrusive ads by default, rewarding creators through Brave Rewards while keeping browsing fast and private. Integrated Tor windows, playlist features, and wallet capabilities give users a modern alternative to traditional browsers.
features: Ad blocking|Tracker protection|Brave Rewards|Tor windows|Crypto wallet

name: Opera Browser
description: Opera Browser offers a built-in VPN, workspace organization, and integrated messengers that streamline multitasking. Pinboards, AI prompts, and modular start pages help users collect inspiration, collaborate, and browse securely without additional extensions.
features: Built-in VPN|Workspaces|Integrated messengers|Pinboards|AI prompts

name: LibreOffice Suite
summary: Open-source office suite for documents and spreadsheets
description: LibreOffice Suite delivers Writer, Calc, Impress, and more in a familiar interface with advanced styles, macro scripting, and compatibility with Microsoft Office formats. Teams produce professional documents offline while organizations customize deployments freely.
features: Writer|Calc|Impress|Draw|Base

name: ONLYOFFICE Desktop Editors
summary: Collaborative office editors with cloud integrations
description: ONLYOFFICE Desktop Editors تدعم DOCX و XLSX و PPTX مع محررات تعاونية، ميزات تتبع التغييرات، وتكاملات سحابية مع Nextcloud و ownCloud. يمكن للشركات إدارة المستندات بأمان مع الحفاظ على التوافق الكامل مع Microsoft 365.
features: Real-time coediting|Cloud integration|Track changes|Document protection|Plugin marketplace

name: WPS Office
summary: Lightweight office suite with cloud templates

features: Writer|Spreadsheets|Presentation|PDF editor|Cloud templates

name: Apache OpenOffice
description: Apache OpenOffice يوفر أدوات Writer و Calc و Impress مع قابلية التمدد عبر الإضافات ومخططات التوافق مع صيغ OpenDocument. تعتمد عليه منظمات غير ربحية وشركات صغيرة لإنشاء مستندات احترافية دون تكاليف ترخيص مرتفعة.
features: Writer|Calc|Impress|Draw|Math

features: TextMaker|PlanMaker|Presentations|Perpetual license|Language tools
